         1)  NWN PvP may have been a complete accident however, it was the ultimate.  To date it WAS perfect.  Have UO and EQ exposed any weaknesses in NWN aside from the lack of 'l337 graf1xz'?<P>2) Politics will be an interesting dynamic in SB however, I doubt a functioning political system will emerge.  More than likely, factions will form quickly and then larger, better organized factions will take them over.  A dominant power will emerge and everyone else will become subordinant.<P>3)  Another case of rock/paper/scissors eh?  If the Werebat/Rogue/BH beats the mage, the mage beats the Beserker/Warlock, and the Beserker/Warlock beats the Werebat/Rogue/BH, where does skill come in? It simply necessitates a sizeable grouping of the respective classes.  No skill, no individual power, just massive, juggernaut-type guilds with power.<P>4)  Two ways to weaken the 24/7 player are the creation of a Rock/Paper/Scissors system and the creation of low limits on levels.  Low level limits are obviously superior to the Rock/Paper/Scissors system unless you happen to be part of a large conglomeration of skillness newbs. <P>5) A wide range of specialties is a nice idea however, unless Wolfpack is somehow able to create a balanced system without the worthless  Rock/Paper/Scissors interface.  Pretty hard to do.<P>Bah, the other points are redundant so I'll end it here.  SB should be a very solid game, however, it won't be perfect.  If ya want perfect, convince a developer that an MMORPG based on a Gold Box game would be the best game ever. Ah shit, none of them give a rat's ass about low end graphics and turn-based PvP.
